This paper proposes a novel ensemble learning method based on Random Forest that incorporates hard example mining and dynamic evolution mechanisms. The paper focuses on improving the accuracy and generalization of the model, which are key topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DM (Data Mining). Additionally, the paper also mentions the use of the model in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE), which are also relevant sub-categories.
